A 34-year-old woman from Mmotwaneng village outside
Groblersdal has gone missing. Cops have launched a massive search operation for Emma
Sithole, it's alleged she went missing on 28 April. Police spokesperson Constable Maphuri Manamela said she was
last seen by her boyfriend at a local tavern. Manamela said Sithole is a mother to a three weeks old infant. According to the cops they have looked for her at friends
and relatives places without any success. Manamela urged anyone with information that can lead to the
victim's whereabouts is requested to contact Captain Mokgoatjana on 0824143244
or call the police emergency toll free number 08600 10111.